Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing after revocation, his probation having been revoked effective 07-19-17.  
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of forty-eight (48) months.   Twenty-four (24) months initial confinement, followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision on each count, concurrent and concurrent with 14 CF 214.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Pay costs of action;
2) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
4) Assessment/treatment/counseing as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
5) AODA assessment and follow through; 
6) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination.  
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given credit for 96 days already served.   
Minutes.

Defendant in custody on another matter.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both or work search;
2) Pay court costs including the $160.00 buy money;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) No possession of any prescription drugs without a valid prescription and if prescribed, taken in prescribed doses;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) no association with any known drug dealers or users;
7) spend four (4) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
